                        <desc>The word God is rubricated in the first three works of <locus target="#ms_i1">fols. ms_i1, </locus>; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two worksof <locus target="#ms_i1">ms_i1</locus></desc>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#114v" facs="119">fols. 114v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#124r #124v" facs="128 129">124r, 124v</locus> (tenth Biblical Canticle).</desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref> is pasted onto the folio. With caption <q>“David, King of Israel with his harp,” in Amharic</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in Amharic and Gǝ‘ǝz: <q>“With her beloved Son, protector of the Ethiopian people, and Redeemer of the World.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc> print card of King <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in Gǝ‘ǝz: <q>“King David.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="004">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus>
                        <desc> print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> is pasted onto the folio. Captions in Cyrillic</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc> print card of Sacred Heart of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> is pasted onto the folio. Caption in French: <q>“N. D. des 3 AVE MARIA. Par votre Puissance, votre Sagesse, votre Misericorde, O Marie Immaculée <gap reason="omitted"/> [illegible].”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">
                        <locus target="#21v" facs="026">Fol. 21v</locus>
                        <desc> a bird, in pencil</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7">
                        <locus target="#135r" facs="139">Fol. 135r</locus>
                        <desc> a print card of “When Paul Met <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1084JesusChrist">JesusChrist</ref>" is pasted onto the folio. Caption is in English: <q>“When Paul Met Jesus. Lesson Material—Acts 9:1–31.  Memory Verse—I am not ashamed of the gospel.” Romans 1:16.”</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8">
                        <locus target="#135v" facs="140">Fol. 135v</locus>
                        <desc> a print card of <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1039Magi">The Three Magi</ref> Note at the bottom: “©Providence Lithograph Co. The World Council of Christian Education NT–A–2.”.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d9">
                    Decorative designs:
                    <locus target="#1r #22r #64r #128r #136r #144r" facs="005 026 068 132 140 148">fols. 1r, 22r, 64r, 128r, 136r, 144r</locus> (haräg);
                    lines of alternating red and black dots are used as section dividers throughout
                    </decoNote>
